UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5263; /* Text0_1: Welcome to our home, $N. Radnaal and I have little to offer, but you are welcome to what hospitality we can provide. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5264; /* Text0_1: My apologies, but you have already learned everything I know. The night elf Faldron could offer you further training, however. Look for him in the Craftsmen\'s Terrace of Darnassus. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5265; /* Text0_1: You need to make your stitches smaller, $N. Fewer items will slip out of your quivers and ammo pouches. Besides, no one likes a lumpy tunic. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5273; /* Text0_1: If you\'re interested in sewing with leather, you\'ve certainly come to the right place. Faldron and Telonis are true artists, and I hope to learn much from them. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5274; /* Text0_1: Oh, I\'m sorry, but you know more about leather than I do at this point. Talk to Faldron over there if you wish to learn more. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5275; /* Text0_1: It\'s so exciting to be here in Darnassus, surrounded by talented people! I just know I\'m going to make my family proud. Maybe if I\'m really lucky, the Sentinels will ask me to join their forces on the front! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5276; /* Text0_1: This hide isn\'t ready to work with yet. I wish it didn\'t take so long to make leather. There has to be some way to cut down on all this waiting. It can\'t be good for my health, you know? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5277; /* Text0_1: Aww, what rotten luck! My skills aren\'t good enough to be of any use to you. Oh well. Talk to Fimble Finespindle over there by the loom. He\'s been working with leather for longer than I have. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5278; /* Text0_1: Oh, goody, something else to do while I wait! You\'re a real life-saver, $N! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5279; /* Text0_1: You like the rug? I killed and skinned the beast myself. May all the centaur fall as easily. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5280; /* Text0_1: I have nothing more to teach you. Talk to Karolek if you wish to further your leatherworking skills. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5281; /* Text0_1: Too bad we can\'t skin the humans and their allies. All that skin is just going to waste. Still, who\'d want to wear the flimsy leather you could make out of it? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5282; /* Text0_1: Skin, glorious skin. It holds your insides... in. You might\'ve noticed my skin\'s not doing so well. To think I used to worry about my pores. Hardly any skin left to worry about these days. In a way, it\'s very freeing. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5283; /* Text0_1: You\'ve got the hang of it. I can\'t teach you any more, but talk to Arthur Moore, a Forsaken who works in the Rogues\' Quarter of the Undercity. Tell him I sent you. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=5284; /* Text0_1: Before the plague came, I knew nothing about leather. Now I know enough to teach others. Death\'s left me with a lot of time on my hands. */
