UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=10686; /* Text0_1: When I first set up my rogue academy in Shattrath, it wasn\'t nearly this crowded. Then, the refugees started flooding in and the naaru needed every available building to house them.$B$BI\'ve closed the doors to my academy for now, but it\'s not permanent. I\'ll find a new place to set up.$B$BThen, a new generation of rogues will learn such staples as the gouge\'n grin, combat looting, and blaming someone else for breaking polymorph. And who can forget the central rule of roguery --- real rogues don\'t feint. */ /* Text1_1: The trick to using evasion is realizing that the best fifteen seconds of your life are often the last. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=10686; /* Text2_1: Swords, claws, daggers, of course -- I\'ve trained rogues in the use of them all. Now maces, I won\'t touch maces and I won\'t instruct any rogue who gets it in his head to wield one.$B$BThere\'s nothing stealthy about a mace. You\'re in for a noisy kill and a long cleanup if you go that route. */ /* Text3_1: My early classes are always filled with bright-eyed young lads. Few make it past the first test, though.$B$BI\'ve given up on shouting, \'when I yell vanish, you need to vanish.\' They never listen. Now, the test simply kills the inept. */
